==英语为主要语言==
{{Main|新加坡英语}}
[[Image:Sing_signroundabout.jpg|thumb]]
[[新加坡英语|新加坡英语]]是新加坡不可或缺的语言。英语被视为新加坡的主要语言，<ref>{{cite journal | url = http://www.leeds.ac.uk/english/staff/afg/pragp3.doc | title = Epistemic modalities and the discourse particles of Singapore | first = A.F. | last = Gupta | editor = Fischer, K. | format = DOC | work = Approaches to Discourse Particles | publisher = Elsevier | location = Amsterdam | pages = 244–263 | journal =  | access-date = 2013-10-15 | archive-date = 2011-02-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110205010214/http://www.leeds.ac.uk/english/staff/afg/pragp3.doc | dead-url = yes }}</ref>在[[新加坡教育|新加坡教育制度]]里，英语是所有的科目（除母语课外）的教学媒介语。<ref name="Dixon, L. Quentin 2005 p. 625-635">Dixon, L. Quentin. (2005). The Bilingual Education Policy in Singapore: Implications for Second Language Acquisition. In James Cohen, J.,  McAlister, K. T., Rolstad, K., and MacSwan,  J (Eds.),  ''ISB4: Proceedings of the 4th International Symposium on Bilingualism''. p. 625-635, Cascadilla Press, Somerville, MA.</ref>英语也是新加坡的行政语言，以及国际商业的重要语言之一。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.moe.gov.sg/media/speeches/2000/sp31032000a.htm |title=31 March 2000 |publisher=Moe.gov.sg |date= |accessdate=2011-01-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120306034004/http://www.moe.gov.sg/media/speeches/2000/sp31032000a.htm |archivedate=2012年3月6日 }}</ref>因为新加坡的殖民历史，新加坡英语按照[[英国英语|英国英语]]的拼法。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blogs.nlb.gov.sg/ask/children/481 |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2011-02-18  |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120303222846/https://blogs.nlb.gov.sg/ask/children/481 |archivedate=2012-03-03 }}</ref>

1819年，当英国人在新加坡建立港口时，英语引入了新加坡。后来，新加坡成为英国殖民地，英语成为行政、法律以及商业语言。随着社会发展与商业变得发达，新加坡发展蒸蒸日上。<ref name="#1">{{Cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/sn.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2014-05-15 |archive-date=2018-12-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225034006/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/sn.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="digital.georgetown.edu">{{cite web | title = Bilingual education with English as an official language: Sociocultural implications | author = Pakir,  Anne | year = 1999 | url = http://repository.library.georgetown.edu/bitstream/handle/10822/551456/gurt-1999.pdf#page=349 | format = PDF | publisher = Georgetown University Press | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/6LktvcHES?url=https://repository.library.georgetown.edu/bitstream/handle/10822/551456/gurt-1999.pdf#page=349 | archivedate = 2013-12-10 }}</ref>

1959年新加坡获得自治以及1965年独立时，当地政府决定保留英语为主要语言，使经济效益最大化。既然英语作为全球商业、科技语言的地位不断上升，推广英语的使用会促进在全球经济的发展，融入全球经济。<ref name="digital.georgetown.edu">{{cite web | title = Bilingual education with English as an official language: Sociocultural implications | author = Pakir,  Anne | year = 1999 | url = http://repository.library.georgetown.edu/bitstream/handle/10822/551456/gurt-1999.pdf#page=349 | format = PDF | publisher = Georgetown University Press | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/6LktvcHES?url=https://repository.library.georgetown.edu/bitstream/handle/10822/551456/gurt-1999.pdf#page=349 | archivedate = 2013-12-10 }}</ref>此外，以英语为通用语是作为新加坡多元种族之间的桥梁。而新加坡的所有学校都改用英语为教学媒介语，就能反映出对英语的重视。1960年代早期直至1970年代后期，由于更多的家长选择让孩子报读英语学校，报读英语小学的的学生从50%剧增至90%。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://libguides.nl.sg/content.php?pid=57257&sid=551371 |work=National Library Board, Singapore |title=Bilingual Education |date=2009-11-12 |accessdate=2010-10-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002211453/http://libguides.nl.sg/content.php?pid=57257&sid=551371 |archivedate=2013-10-02 }}</ref>就读华语、马来语、淡米尔语学校的学生因而下降，导致学校关闭。原以华语教学的[[南洋大学_(新加坡)|南洋大学]]，雖然受到華人社群的阻力，但也改用英语为教学媒介语。<ref>Deterding, David. (2007). Singapore English. Edinburgh University Press.</ref>

多年来，英语的使用急剧增加。<ref>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Singapore English definition - Dictionary - MSN Encarta |url=http://encarta.msn.com/encnet/features/dictionary/DictionaryResults.aspx?refid=1861728232 |work= |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5kwsaTgez?url=http://encarta.msn.com/encnet/features/dictionary/DictionaryResults.aspx?refid=1861728232 |archivedate=2009-11-01 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>新加坡目前是全亚洲最精通英语的国家。<ref name="Healy Consultants">{{cite web|title=Singapore Company Registration and Formation|url=http://www.healyconsultants.com/company-incorporation/singapore-company-incorporation.html|publisher=Healy Consultants|accessdate=19 August 2013|archive-date=2013-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130728124721/http://www.healyconsultants.com/company-incorporation/singapore-company-incorporation.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2009年12月，教育部长[[黄永宏|黄永宏]]指出，新加坡把英语作为家庭用语有上升的趋势。2009年报读小学的学生当中，华族和印度族学生有60%在家中主要讲英语，马来族学生有35%在家中主要讲英语。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.straitstimes.com/BreakingNews/Singapore/Story/STIStory_471530.html | work=The Straits Times | location=Singapore | title=Refine bilingual policy | first=Amelia | last=Tan | date=2009-12-29 | accessdate=2010-11-11 | archive-date=2009-12-31 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091231092113/http://www.straitstimes.com/BreakingNews/Singapore/Story/STIStory_471530.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>总体来讲，在新加坡，孩子上小学的家庭有56%主要使用英语。英语是32%的新加坡人的母语，但若是把第二语言使用者包括在内，英语就是新加坡人使用最多的语言。<ref name="ReferenceC">[http://www.singstat.gov.sg/pubn/papers/people/c2000adr-literacy.pdf Literacy and language]  {{webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/5oFD4Gdnx?url=http://www.singstat.gov.sg/pubn/papers/people/c2000adr-literacy.pdf |date=2010-03-15 }}, Singapore Census of Population, 2000. Singapore Department of Statistics (December 2000).</ref>[[新加坡式英语|新加坡式英语]]，英语的混合语，在岛上也广泛使用。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nbu.bg/PUBLIC/IMAGES/File/departamenti/4ujdi%20ezitsi%20i%20literaturi/Doklad_Adrien_2.pdf |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2010-04-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101127055450/http://nbu.bg/PUBLIC/IMAGES/File/departamenti/4ujdi%20ezitsi%20i%20literaturi/Doklad_Adrien_2.pdf |archivedate=2010-11-27 }}.</ref>然而，当地政府较倾向于标准英语。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,501020729-322685,00.html | work=Time | title=A War of Words Over 'Singlish' | date=2002-07-22 | accessdate=2013-10-16 | archive-date=2013-08-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130806210202/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,501020729-322685,00.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>

